# VISION
Build a small web service that lets users create, update, and share short notes with AI-assisted summaries.

## Problem
Teams scatter notes across tools; nothing stays in sync or is searchable.

## Goal
Create a lightweight, searchable notes service with AI summarization for each note.

## Success Criteria
- Users can create, edit, and delete notes.
- Notes are searchable by title and content.
- AI can generate or regenerate a short summary per note.

# CONTEXT

## Target Audience
- Small product / engineering teams (3–10 people).

## Technical Environment
- Backend: Node.js / TypeScript
- Storage: PostgreSQL
- Frontend: React or similar SPA

## Constraints
- Keep infrastructure simple (single region, no hard multi-tenancy).
- Must be usable locally with Docker.

# STRUCTURE

## System Architecture
- API service (REST/JSON)
- Database (PostgreSQL)
- Background worker for AI summarization

## Data Model
- `users` (id, email, name)
- `notes` (id, user_id, title, body, summary, created_at, updated_at)

## Decisions
- Start with server-side rendered HTML for simplicity; add SPA later if needed.
- Use OpenAI-compatible API for summaries; abstract via a small adapter.

# PLAN

## Phase 1 — Core CRUD (Week 1)
- Basic API for notes (create/read/update/delete).
- Simple HTML UI for listing and editing notes.

## Phase 2 — Search & Auth (Week 2)
- Full-text search on notes.
- Email-based login (magic link or password).

## Phase 3 — AI Summaries (Week 3)
- Integrate AI provider for generating note summaries.
- Add “Regenerate summary” button per note.

# TASKS

- [ ] Set up project structure and tooling
- [ ] Define DB schema for users and notes
- [ ] Implement notes CRUD API
- [ ] Build minimal HTML UI for notes
- [ ] Add search endpoint and UI
- [ ] Integrate auth (email login)
- [ ] Implement AI summary adapter
- [ ] Add “generate summary” endpoint and UI action

